<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11125b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11125b">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11125b"> 125(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dauphin ~ <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n11125b"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Charles X &agrave; Prague</b> &hellip; Il m&apos;&eacute;tait impossible de retrouver la voix, en regardant dans la demeure des empereurs d&apos;Autriche le soixante-huiti&egrave;me roi de France, courb&eacute; sous le poids de ces r&egrave;gnes et de soixanteseize ann&eacute;es: de ces ann&eacute;es, vingt-quatre s&apos;&eacute;taient &eacute;coul&eacute;es dans l&apos;exil, cinq sur un tr&ocirc;ne chancelant; le monarque achevait ses derniers jours dans un dernier exil, avec le petit-fils dont le p&egrave;re avait &eacute;t&eacute; assassin&eacute; et de qui la m&egrave;re &eacute;tait captive. Charles X, pour rompre ce silence, m&apos;adressa quelques questions. Alors j&apos;expliquai bri&egrave;vement l&apos;objet de mon voyage: je me dis porteur d&apos;une lettre de madame la duchesse de Berry adress&eacute;e &agrave; madame la Dauphine, dans laquelle la prisonni&egrave;re de Blaye confiait le soin de ses enfants &agrave; la prisonni&egrave;re du Temple, comme ayant la pratique du malheur. <br><font color="green">[Charles welcomes Chateaubriand]</font> His eyes were moist; he had me sit down by a small wooden table, on which stood two candles; he sat down next to the same table, leaning toward me his good ear, the better to hear me, thus drawing my attention to his years, which mingled their common infirmities with the extraordinary calamities of his life. / It was impossible for me to find my voice, looking at the <mark>sixty-eighth king</mark> of France in the home of the emperors of Austria, bowed down with the weight of these reigns and of his seventy-six years.] <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 170</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n18049a" href="n18all.htm#n18049a">N18 (VI.B.8):049(a)</a> and <a name="n19189g" href="n19all.htm#n19189g">N19 (VI.B.19):189(g)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
